# Release Version Alignment

- When preparing a release, update `EchoesOfAzeroth_ZulAman.toc` so `## Version:` matches the intended release number exactly.
- Create the Git tag in the form `vX.Y.Z`, and keep it aligned with the `.toc` version `X.Y.Z`.
- Keep the release workflow tag convention aligned with semantic version tags prefixed by `v`.
- Before tagging, double-check that the version in the `.toc`, the commit intent, and the release tag all refer to the same release.
